On July 6, 2009, Vice President Biden hosted two conference calls with governors and mayors/county executives to discuss the implementation of the Recovery Act. The calls included participants such as Governor Chet Culver, Governor Jennifer Granholm, Governor Tim Pawlenty, Governor Rick Perry, Governor Jodi Rell, Mayor Dave Bing, Mayor-President Joey Durel, Mayor Ashley Swearengin, Mayor Charlie Tomlinson, and County Executive Pete Kremen. The purpose of the calls was to discuss the progress and challenges of implementing the Recovery Act.